#!/bin/sh
# Man-style overview of the in-box nixgen tools. Single source for
# in-box documentation; update-test asserts every installed nixgen-*
# binary is mentioned here, so additions fail loud when undocumented.
# usage: nixgen-help
page() {
cat <<'EOF'
NIXGEN(7)                  nixstore generations                  NIXGEN(7)

NAME
       nixgen - Arch Linux generations on the nix store layer

DESCRIPTION
       The root filesystem is an immutable, content-addressed
       generation in a nix store, overlay-mounted at boot with a tmpfs
       upper. GRUB picks the generation; rollback is booting an older
       entry. Uncommitted writes live in RAM and vanish at reboot:
       commit what you want to keep.

COMMANDS
       nixgen-commit <name> [store-root]
              Import the running root onto the store disk (initializes
              a blank one) + GRUB entry. Reboot, it's in the menu.

       nixgen-update <name> [cmd]
              Build the next generation offline (default pacman -Syu)
              with its upper on the store disk; the live root and its
              module tree stay intact. Reboot to switch. No-op runs
              bail without importing: a db pre-check skips the build
              entirely (default cmd only), and an unchanged tree after
              any cmd skips the import.

       nixgen-switch <name>
              Soft-reboot into another generation, the fast path for
              same-kernel changes (userspace restarts in seconds). The
              kernel and already-loaded modules stay resident; fresh
              module loads come from the target's matching tree, so
              targets without modules for the running kernel are
              refused (kernel updates need a real reboot into their
              entry). Ephemeral like any boot: fresh upper, GRUB
              default unchanged.

       nixgen-remove <basename>...
              Delete committed generations (GC codepath, refuses the
              running one) + prune their GRUB entries.

       nixgen-listid
              Generations visible to the box: short hash id, source
              (disk/iso), running marker. Ids are accepted by -switch,
              -remove and -diffid as unique hash prefixes: reference a
              generation by id when names collide.

       nixgen-diffid <name> <name> [subpath]
              Systemwide diff of two generations: every added/removed/
              changed file, content-compared (near-free on deduped
              stores). Subpath = full content diff of that subtree.
              Ownership/mode deltas appear as the etc/nixgen/perms
              diff.

       Box-to-box shipping rides the installed primitives.
       export-path re-hashes against the db so local corruption cannot
       spread; import-path refuses content that does not hash back to
       its claimed store path and dedups on arrival:
              export-path /nixstoredev <basename>... > bundle
              import-path /nixstoredev < bundle

       nixgen-adopt <store-path-basename> [store-root]
              Give a received generation its GRUB entry (same stanza
              nixgen-commit appends). Refuses paths without a
              kernel+initramfs and duplicate entries.

       nixgen-data <partition> [--fs <type>]
              Format a partition as the persistent data disk (label
              NIXDATA) and seed it from the running root. Paths listed
              in /etc/nixgen/state (default /home and /var/log) then
              mount from it on any boot whose GRUB entry carries
              nixdata=NIXDATA; commit excludes them, so that state
              flows forward across generations instead of rolling back
              with them. Opt-in per entry: without the flag (or the
              disk) those paths stay in the RAM upper as usual.
              Committed/updated entries inherit the flag from the
              running cmdline. --fs as in nixgen-setup (ext4 default).

       nixgen-setup <device> [name] [--fs <type>] [--data <size>]
              Install onto a disk from inside the box: GPT (ESP +
              NIXSTORE), standalone GRUB, fresh store seeded with a
              commit of the running root. --fs picks the store filesystem (ext4 default,
              also btrfs, xfs, f2fs); run without arguments to list
              them. --data carves a NIXDATA partition of <size> on the
              same disk (same fs), seeds it and stamps nixdata=NIXDATA
              into the installed entry: single-disk persistent state
              without a separate nixgen-data run. GRUB has to read the store to load a generation's
              kernel, which is what limits the choice. Deps (grub,
              dosfstools, the filesystem's own progs) install on demand
              into the ephemeral upper: needs network, gone at reboot.
              UEFI only; unplug a NIXSTORE-labeled installer stick
              before first boot (GRUB searches by label).

INTERNALS
       nixgen-savemeta <root>
              Capture what the store import canonicalises away (modes,
              ownership incl. symlinks, capabilities, POSIX ACLs) into
              etc/nixgen/{perms,caps,acls}; runs before every import.

       nixgen-restmeta [root]
              Replay that manifest; runs at boot (nixgen-perms.service)
              and inside build sandboxes.

       nixgen-getty
              Conditional autologin shim for agetty: prompt-free only
              while root is passwordless. passwd root restores login
              prompts, but the password lives in the tmpfs upper like
              any write: nixgen-commit it, or a reboot is passwordless
              autologin again.

       nixgen-help
              This page.

       Off the command surface (/usr/local/lib): nixgen-entry writes
       entries.cfg atomically and GC-roots the entry's generation
       (shared by commit/update/adopt); nixgen-seedstate first-time
       seeds state dirs onto the data partition. A system generator
       (nixgen-data-generator) turns nixdata=<label> plus the manifest
       into the /run/nixdata mount and the per-path binds.

FILES
       /nixstore                     store holding the running generation
       /nixstoredev                  store-disk root (when attached)
       /nixstoredev/entries.cfg      GRUB menu of committed generations
       /run/nixgen-active            live generation after a soft switch
       /run/nixdata                  data partition (nixdata= boots)
       etc/nixgen/{perms,caps,acls}  metadata manifests, per generation
       etc/nixgen/state              paths that ride the data partition

NIXGEN(7)                  nixstore generations                  NIXGEN(7)
EOF
}
if [ -t 1 ]; then
	page | ${PAGER:-more}
else
	page
fi
